{% extends 'layouts/base.njk' %}

{% block header %}
{% include 'components/header.njk' %}
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<main id="content">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-content p-base px-lg bg-card rounded-md shadow-md" x-data="registerEventbrite">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-none md:text-5xl text-header mb-base">{{title}}</h1>
        <div class="prose max-w-content2">
            <p>We're stoked that you're planning on joining us for Go Play NW's online event for Fall 2022! Once we get you through our quick 5-step registration process you'll be ready to play some games!</p>
            <h2>1. Create a GoPlayNW.org account</h2>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="notAuth">
                <p>To get the most out of your Go Play NW experience, you'll need to have a GoPlayNW.org account. Once you're registered for the event, you can use your account to sign up for games on our <a href="/events">Game Schedule</a>, <a href="/run-an-event">run a game</a>, or for <a href="/volunteer-shifts">volunteer shifts</a>.</p>
                <p><a class="icon-new-user" href="/create-account">Create a Go Play NW account</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="isAuth">
                <p>You have already created your account.</p>
                <p class="icon-checkmark">Continue to step 2 below</p>
            </div>
            <h2>2. Log in to your GoPlayNW.org account</h2>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="notAuth">
                <p>Once you have a GoPlayNW.org account, you'll need to be logged in before registering for the event so we can link your GoPlayNW.org account to your Eventbrite registration.</p>
                <button class="icon-login" @click="modal='login'">Login to your Go Play NW account</button>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="isAuth">
                <p>You have already logged into your GoPlayNW.org account.
                <p class="icon-checkmark">Continue to step 3 below</p>
            </div>
            <h2>3. Link your GoPlayNW.org account to Eventbrite</h2>
                <p>
                    Now the magic happens! Go Play NW uses <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/">Eventbrite</a> to handle ticketing for our online
                    events. In order to connect your Eventbrite registration to your game schedule for the weekend, we need your permission to link your Go Play NW and Eventbrite accounts.
                </p>
                <p>When linking your Go Play NW account with your Eventbrite account, you will be taken to the Eventbrite website where you will be asked to login to your Eventbrite account.</P>
                <p>Once you're logged in to Eventbrite, you will be asked if you want to allow Go Play NW to access your Eventbrite account.</p>
                </p>
                    <img src="/static/images/eventbrite_example.png" class="w-full h-full object-contain" alt="An example of what the official Eventbrite approval page should look like.">
                <p>
                    Click "Allow," and you will be brought back to the Go Play NW website so you can complete your ticket purchase.
                </p>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="notAuth">
                <button @click="modal='login'" class="icon-login">Login to link your Go Play NW and Eventbrite accounts.</button>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="isAuth">
                <a class="icon-eventbrite" href="https://www.eventbrite.com/oauth/authorize?response_type=code&client_id=XDAPRWGTYCXDSNF723">Link your Go Play NW and Eventbrite accounts</a>
            </div>
            <h2>4. Buy your ticket!</h2>
            <p>Once you've linked your Eventbrite and Go Play NW accounts, Eventbrite will bring you back to the Go Play NW website where you can purchase your ticket to the event.</p>
            <p>
                Please only purchase 1 ticket to the event per Go Play NW account. If you want to buy a ticket for someone else, the best way to do that is to just have the other person (or people!)
                "purchase" their own ticket for $0. Remember, the event is Pay What You Want, so it's totally cool! If you want to give us a little extra to cover your friends too!
            </p>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="notAuth">
                <button @click="modal='login'" class="icon-login">Login to buy your ticket.</button>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="isAuth">
                <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/oauth/authorize?response_type=code&client_id=XDAPRWGTYCXDSNF723" class="icon-ticket-solid">Buy your ticket!</a>
            </div>
            <h2>5. Get involved!</h2>
            <p>It's attendees like you that make Go Play NW great! Now that you've got your ticket, let's help you get the most out of your Go Play NW experience!</p>
            <p><a href="https://discord.gg/AqhayGFexQ" class="icon-discord">Join our Community Discord</a></p>
            <p><a href="/events" class="icon-calendar-clock">Sign up to play in a scheduled game</a></p>
            <p><a href="/run-an-event" class="icon-dice">Run a game for the weekend</a></p>
            <p><a href="/the-donut" class="icon-donut">Learn about the Donut</a></p>
            <p><a href="/contact-us" class="icon-envelope">Questions? Contact us</a></p>
            <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-highlight">Let's get you registered for Go Play NW Online!</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="notAuth">
                <button @click="modal='login'" class="icon-login">Login to your Go Play NW account to get started.</button>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-content2" x-cloak x-show="isAuth">
                <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/oauth/authorize?response_type=code&client_id=XDAPRWGTYCXDSNF723" class="icon-ticket-solid">Buy your ticket!</a>
            </div>
            <div></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>
{% endblock %}

